#### Overload 3: Multiple Signals with Render Function

```tsx
rx({ user, posts }, (awaited, loadables) => {
  return <div>{awaited.user.name}</div>;
});
```

**When to use:**

- Multiple signals
- Complex rendering logic
- Manual loading states
- Most powerful and common pattern

**Two access modes:**

**Mode 1: Suspense (awaited)**

```tsx
rx({ user, posts }, (awaited) => {
  // Throws promise if loading
  // awaited.user and awaited.posts are resolved values
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{awaited.user.name}</h1>
      <PostList posts={awaited.posts} />
    </div>
  );
});
```

**Mode 2: Manual Loading States (loadables)**

```tsx
rx({ user, posts }, (awaited, loadables) => {
  if (loadables.user.status === "loading") {
    return <Spinner />;
  }

  if (loadables.user.status === "error") {
    return <Error error={loadables.user.error} />;
  }

  // loadables.user.status === 'success'
  return <div>{loadables.user.value.name}</div>;
});
```

**Lazy tracking:**

```tsx
// Only subscribes to signals you actually access!
rx({ user, posts, comments, likes }, (awaited) => {
  // Only accesses user - only subscribes to user
  return <div>{awaited.user.name}</div>;
});

// ‚ùå Bad: Accessing all upfront
rx({ user, posts, comments }, (awaited) => {
  const u = awaited.user; // Subscribes
  const p = awaited.posts; // Subscribes (unnecessary!)
  const c = awaited.comments; // Subscribes (unnecessary!)
  return <div>{u.name}</div>; // Only uses user
});
```

**Conditional access:**

```tsx
rx({ user, settings }, (awaited) => {
  if (!awaited.user.isAdmin) {
    return <div>Access denied</div>;
  }

  // Only accesses settings if user is admin
  return <AdminPanel settings={awaited.settings} />;
});
```

**With watch option:**

```tsx
// Memoize render function with watch dependencies
rx(
  { user, posts },
  (awaited) => {
    return <div>{formatUser(awaited.user, locale)}</div>;
  },
  {
    watch: [locale], // Re-create render when locale changes
  }
);
```

**Complete loading pattern:**

```tsx
rx({ data }, (awaited, loadables) => {
  const { status, value, error, promise } = loadables.data;

  switch (status) {
    case "loading":
      return <Spinner />;

    case "error":
      return (
        <ErrorBoundary error={error}>
          <button onClick={() => promise.retry()}>Retry</button>
        </ErrorBoundary>
      );

    case "success":
      return <DataView data={value} />;
  }
});
```

